<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Prey2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Prey,</orth> vb. to chase and feed on animals: <bibl n="shak. ado 5.3.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 3, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.133" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.71" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 71</bibl> (the later Qq <emph>may p.;</emph> the earlier Qq and Ff <emph>make p.</emph>). <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.263" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 263</bibl>. With <cit><quote>on:</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.119" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 119</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.7.15" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 7, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.1.90" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 1, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.57" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 2, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 199</bibl> (O. Edd. <emph>in reason</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>